tsächlich nur für phonologische Phänomene bekannt war. Während die nach Norden wandernde Perfektexpansion ein Verdrängungsprozess des Präteritums durch das Perfekt ist, verdrängen Präteritum und Plusquamperfekt die Tempora Perfekt und Doppelperfekt nicht. Stattdessen hat sich ein System aus vier komplementären Vergangenheitstempora im Alemannischen Deutschlands etabliert.  aIn this volume, corpus-linguistic methods and spontaneous language data have been utilized to prove that the tense forms preterite and pluperfect have reestablished themselves in German Alemannic. The reason for this is the influence of standard language. The partial reversal of the disappearance of the preterite is not process of suppression; rather, the four tenses praeterite, perfect, pluperfect and double perfect form a complementary system.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Universitätsbibliothek Freiburg  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aDialektologie. 4aDoppelperfekt. 4aMorphologie. 4aPräteritum.  aDialectology.  aDouble Perfect.  aMorphology.  aPreterit.2 aUniversitätsbibliothek Freiburgefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022z9783110993684oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107651510 cprintz978311076508340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110765113zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110765113zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110765113/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23